post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'While neither seems acceptable, most would rather face prejudice than prison. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Some of this emotional harm is directly caused by erroneous negative perceptions of drug use like the ones being perpetrated here. Many people are unfairly vilified for responsibly using drugs, simply because they are illegal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The correlation between drug use and crime is fuelled at least partly by prohibition.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Fewer [productive](https://www.houstonchronicle.com/business/outside-the-boardroom/article/Mass-incarceration-hurts-U-S-economy-7434722.php) people will be in jail. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug use correlates negatively with socially-responsible behavior. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is a false equivalency. Providing a service or good to bolster economic growth is not the same as being forced to give your money to the government.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It also means there will be less demand for young people as workers in the black market. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalization will not drastically affect drug use. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Personal autonomy](https://www.law.cornell.edu/wex/personal_autonomy) is not a fundamental right in the US constitution.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs could be legalised in government shops in which they could be administered through government pharmacists. This would allow governments to control access, much like the [Swedish alcohol trade](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Systembolaget).'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The prosecution takes place after the repercussions have occurred. A ban can prevent them from ever happening.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Cocaine is [highly addictive](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cocaine_dependence) and easy to become dependent on. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Selling harmful products is a poor long-term business strategy, as can be seen with tobacco companies. It only works as long as there is uncertainty in their harms. When the harms become apparent, people will take measures to stop using it as well as take measures to stop others from using it.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Recreational drugs can be used as self medication especially for those with severe mental health issues like PTSD and psychosis.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The culture of [overprescription](https://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2018/06/opioid-epidemic/563576/) in the medical community has been a significant factor in the opioid crisis. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Tracing a car owner by his license plate after causing a severe accident with people killed does not undo the accident either. But it creates a moral barrier for people, so they think twice before doing such a hit and run. Same goes for traceable drugs. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalising drugs would be damaging for public health. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The [relatives](https://novarecoverycenter.com/drug-use/parental-drug-abuse/) of addicts are negatively impacted by their addiction. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '"Giving up" is preferable to endlessly pursuing an unobtainable goal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Criminals will have to either adapt or lose the income that prevents their other crimes from catching up with them.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'An overdose of heroin is usually fatal without medical help; [during 2016](https://www.cdc.gov/drugoverdose/data/heroin.html), almost 15,500 people died from drug overdoses involving heroin in the United States.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If drugs other than alcohol were legalized, alcohol sales would plummet, and a lot of jobs in the alcohol industry would disappear.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "In countries where using marijuana is legal or allowed, [smoking games](https://honestmarijuana.com/weed-games/) have arisen to get more stoned/high more quickly. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Education on how to be safe with drugs can be seen as an incentive to use them. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Sobriety may be required for the optimal exercise of rational moral agency; however, it is not required for the generell exercise of rational moral agency. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The [global financial crisis](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Financial_crisis_of_2007%E2%80%932008) was caused by big companies acting with only their profits in mind, and the detrimental effects are still felt today. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help patients by facilitating access to medicines \\(drugs\\) that are currently hard to obtain. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Removing some of these constraints through the legalisation of drugs could make studies more successful.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The "[27 club](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/27_Club)" is an infamous list of artists who died from overdosing on drugs at the age of 27. That\'s why drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Evidence suggests that [addiction is not caused by drugs](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ao8L-0nSYzg) but by social problems.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is little medical discrimination for those who use legal harmful substances such as alcohol or tobacco.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Someone experiencing elevated stress levels isn't a good enough justification to limit other people's freedom by force. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "If you plan to drug someone with the intent of raping them, you're also able to get a hold of the something as ubiquitous as a benzodiazepine."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Because pain is an important clinical symptom, legal recreational opioids may delay patients from seeking care in a timely fashion.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "In countries where using marijuana is legal or allowed, [smoking games](https://honestmarijuana.com/weed-games/) have arisen to get more stoned/high more quickly. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is a tautological argument, presupposing that prohibiting drugs is morally right.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The government specifies what is unacceptable through prohibition. Taxation is how the government discourages. The government is only "encouraging" if they provide aid or assistance.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The "[27 club](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/27_Club)" is an infamous list of artists who died from overdosing on drugs at the age of 27. That\'s why drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Entheogenic drugs](https://maps.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=5468), such as psychedelics, have been used throughout human history for many benefits in evolutionary growth and cognitive development.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There will be less smuggling and less drug-caused conflict. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Tobacco farming before abolition was [done by slaves](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tobacco_in_the_American_colonies). So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The black market businesses won't be able to invest in productivity-increasing \\(especially immovable\\) capital, as the threat of being caught discourages such investments. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Giving a legal framework to the use of certain drugs may help to prevent the development of infectious diseases.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The climb out of poverty is not helped by wasting resources on ingesting toxic materials.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is possible that decriminalization dissuades those who specifically start using drugs as a way of breaking the law, such as [early data from Portugal](https://www.leafly.com/news/politics/portugal-drug-decriminalization-statistics) suggests. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Currently, in many countries, stores which sell age-restricted products such as alcohol have strict regulations in place to ensure the consumer is of appropriate age. The same could be done with other drugs. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug legalisation would mean governments get to suggest a recommended dose, preventing the incidence of death by overdose. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Using a fake ID in a legal establishment implies much more work and risk than just buying from the unregulated black market.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Many Canadian cigarettes are [smuggled back](https://www.publicsafety.gc.ca/cnt/rsrcs/pblctns/archive-stts-cntrbnd-tbcc/index-en.aspx) into Canada.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'In many legal frameworks, the use of drugs is not considered a criminal offense. Only production, commerce, ownership and distribution of drugs are typically illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In Colorado, between 2014 and 2017, [over $500 million](https://money.cnn.com/2017/07/19/news/colorado-marijuana-tax-revenue/index.html) in government revenue was raised by taxes and fees on marijuana sales. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Established companies would be strictly controlled.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If recreational drugs were legal, social events such as parties would have more variety. Drug-friendly events would also have no cause for paranoia. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It can be argued that the terms 'recreational' and 'medicinal' are interchangeable. So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the US, more people are addicted to work or shopping than to all illicit drugs combined \\([2010](https://filtermag.org/2018/09/25/the-invisible-majority-people-whose-drug-use-is-not-problematic/)\\). I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The number of deaths from overdose will rise dramatically as a result of easy access to drugs including meth, MDMA, and heroin. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's people's own choice whether to be moral or not. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Taking drugs is not always a victimless crime, as drug users can harm others.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A victim of such an act would not fear prosecution for consumption if drugs were legal, and therefore would more easily seek and obtain help and/or retribution.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Both of these "contracts" are often initiated under desperate circumstances or by ill informed people.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Several 'great' artists have died from an overdose on drugs and thus actually causing negative contributions to human culture as the world is deprived of their 'artwork'."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Opiates, such as heroin, are very detrimental to a persons health. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This claim is speculative. The correlation between drugs and \\(violent\\) crime is observable. The causes for that correlation are not necessarily observable.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The logic of this argument would necessitate prohibition of alcohol, along with cigarettes, prescription painkillers, household cleaning products, motor vehicles, power tools; and anything a person may use to end their life consciously or accidentally. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legal drugs make it easier for criminals to coerce prostitutes through drug addiction with the state being able to do less to rehabilitate them forcefully. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Fewer [productive](https://www.houstonchronicle.com/business/outside-the-boardroom/article/Mass-incarceration-hurts-U-S-economy-7434722.php) people will be in jail. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing something means including it the current system of business oversight and regulation as other legal activities. This means documenting purchases and monetary transactions, as well as filing and paying taxes. This means more control over where drugs come from and money goes, rather than would be the case under prohibition or decriminalization.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It can be argued that the terms 'recreational' and 'medicinal' are interchangeable. So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Cocaine addiction causes [higher impulsivity](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5817335/), meaning sufferers are more likely to engage in risky behaviour such as gambling. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing marijuana will increase the risk of accidents on the highways \\(and indeed has in [Washington, Oregon and Colorado](http://fortune.com/2018/10/18/legal-marijuana-car-accidents-study/) where it has been legalized\\) causing harm to others.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Established companies selling drugs could be just as dangerous \\(to society\\) as criminals.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Since access to drugs is limited, and alcohol is widely available, this is to be expected and not proof of success.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Young people could use fake IDs to buy drugs, the same way they currently do with alcohol and cigarettes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs have recreational and social value.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the Andes, [coca](https://nacla.org/article/beat-goes-us-war-coca), a sacred plant harmful when mass produced as a cash crop, has replaced the production of fruits and vegetables.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The risk of MDMA is not higher than many sports. MDMA has been compared to [horseback riding](http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk/7876425.stm) in terms of risks. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug prohibition might be inspired by some kind of racism but abandoning it would not necessarily mean an improvement of the situation for those incarcerated or addicted to drugs. There are still many other systematic racial issues unrelated to drug prohibition.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "When drugs are legal, health institutions can give people valuable information on how much you can take and other health advice on drugs. Now they can't because they would 'support' taking drugs and so also 'support' something illegal. I believe all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is because the US prison system is [privately owned.](https://smartasset.com/mortgage/the-economics-of-the-american-prison-system) Incentive structures mean that running prisons can only be profitable with high rates of incarceration.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Benzodiazepines are [readily available](http://w-bad.org/statistics/) in most countries for common complaints like insomnia, jet lag and performance anxiety, and are actually more effective at increasing the effects of alcohol than barbiturates.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The first [anti-cocaine laws](http://www.drugpolicy.org/issues/brief-history-drug-war) in the early 1900s were directed at black men in the South.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The availability of drugs is not the cause of suicides. It is just the means to do it. If they are not available other means will be found.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Affordable drugs will more likely lessen the negative impacts of drug use, as overall users would be less likely to abuse substances due to psychological distress caused by financial instability.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing all drugs will lead to much larger societal rifts: Drug usage is higher among the poor and socially marginalized, which in turn makes their condition worse.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is not mutually exclusive with legalizing drugs. Both could be done. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Further studies on the "Rat Park" experiment discussed in the video [have found](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rat_Park#Reaction_to_the_experiment) social isolation is not necessary for addiction.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are more effective policies than legalizing drug use to challenge drug abuse.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Safety of irresponsible people shouldn't come at the expense of freedom of responsible people."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Criminalising the activity of drug users has negative effects on individuals, their families, and society. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Having drugs be both illegal and valuable has funded extensive infrastructure for smuggling things across the US border.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Based on countries that have decriminalized drugs like [Portugal](https://borgenproject.org/decriminalization-of-drugs-in-portugal/), drug use has not significantly increased among the poor population, or at all.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'US states that have legalised marijuana have seen a lot of benefits.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization reduces the danger of overdosing.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'For a drug user incarceration is much [more expensive](http://www.bhsbaltimore.org/site/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Incarceration-vs-Drug-Treatment-Costs.pdf) than treatment, particularly as many drug users are productive members of society.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Former inmates are significantly more at risk of drug-related mortality than the general population.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization reduces the danger of overdosing.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is preferable that if people are going to take drugs, the profit of the industry go to the government to use to provide important services rather than to gangs or drug cartels. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Although social prejudice may remain, addicts could seek help far easier if there were no fear of legal repercussions.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The negative repercussions of drug use should be prosecuted on their own merit and context \\(without prosecuting the drug use itself\\).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Someone experiencing elevated stress levels isn't a good enough justification to limit other people's freedom by force. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
